%General%

           Welcome to Z-Mail 5.0!
  
With Z-Mail, you can read and reply to your incoming mail, send new
messages, save messages, print messages, search, and do many more
mail-related functions.  Most anything that you might wish to do with
electronic mail messages can be done with Z-Mail in one way or
another.  
  
@@ifdef ZMAIL_BASIC
Many of the common tasks can be found in the ~#Main Window#~'s
menubar, where pulldown menus provide access to most Z-Mail
functions.  There is also the ~#Button panel#~ containing 
pushbuttons that are equivalent to many common menu items.
@@else
Many of the common tasks can be found in the ~#Main Window#~'s
menubar, where pulldown menus provide access to most Z-Mail
functions.  There is also the ~#Button panel#~ that contains
user-defined pushbuttons.
@@endif ZMAIL_BASIC
%%<Help
%%

%Help%
Help is available in most parts of the application.  Most dialogs have
a Help button in the lower right corner or a Help menu on the right
side of the menubar, if one exists.  Help information guides you
through common tasks, and shows correct usage for commands and
techniques for interacting with Z-Mail dialogs.

The "Click for Help" Help menu item changes to pointer to a hand.  When
the pointer is a hand, move the pointer to the area for which you need
help and click the left mouse button.  The ~#Help Index#~ dialog will
appear, displaying help information for the item you clicked.

@@ifndef ZMAIL_BASIC
Help for Z-Script commands is accessed either by typing "help <command>"
or "? <command>" in the Command Area of the main Z-Mail Window
(replace <command> with the command name on which you want help).

The "?" command lists all the Z-Script commands.
@@endif
%%

%Help Index%
%help_index_dialog%
Click a topic in the left hand list of the Help Index dialog to see
help in the text field to the right.

Words that are underlined have corresponding entries elsewhere in the
help text.  If you double-click on underlined words, you'll be taken
to the corresponding ~#help#~ entry.  For example, if you double-click on
the following word:

       ~#Attachments~ui#~
 
then you'll jump to the ~#help#~ entry describing Z-Mail attachments.

You may also type a phrase into the "Search For" text field and click the
Search button to search the entire help text for the phrase.
Subsequent clicks of the Search button will find subsequent
occurrences of the phrase.
