%Opening Folders%
%open_folder_dialog%
%Open Folder dialog%
To open a folder:

   - Choose the Open... item from the Folder menu
     on the Main Window.

The "Open..." menu item brings up a ~#File Finder#~ where you choose the
folder to open.  Click "Open" to open the folder.  Click "Search" to
show the contents of a selected directory.

Folders may be opened "read-only" by setting the "Read Only"
radio button.  You cannot change a folder that is opened read-only, and it
loads somewhat faster, since Z-Mail does not have to make a temporary
working copy.

If you lack permissions to modify the folder, Z-Mail will
automatically mark the folder read-only, even if the "Read Only"
radio button is not selected.

To see only files that are mail folders, set the "Folders Only"
toggle. To see files with names that begin with ".",
set the "Hidden Files" toggle.
%%

%Removing Folders%
To remove a folder:

   -  choose the Remove...  item from the Folder
      menu in the ~#Main Window#~.  

The "Remove..." item brings up a ~#File Finder#~ where you
choose the folder to removed.  Click "Remove" to remove
the selected folder.  If you have selected a directory
in the file list, click "Search" to show its contents.
%%

%Renaming Folders%
To rename a folder:

   - choose the Rename... item from the Folder menu
     on the Main Window.

The Rename... item brings up a ~#File Finder#~ where you
choose the folder to renamed.  The name of the selected
file appears in the Old Name box.  Specify the new name
for the folder in the New Name box, and click OK. 

If you have selected a directory
in the file list, click "Search" to show its contents.
%%

%Closing Folders%
To close a folder:

  - choose the Close Folder item from the Folder menu on the
    Main Window.

You may only close the folder that is currently "active".
%%<Folder Popup

%Folder Popup%
The Folder popup menu on the Folder Panel of the ~#Main Window#~
contains the names of all open folders. To make an open folder
the active one, select its name from the menu.

If you close one or more folders, the 'Reopen...' item is added to the
popup. When you choose Reopen..., a dialog appears listing all the
folders that you opened and subsequently closed.  You may re-open one
of the listed folders by double-clicking it.
%%

%-shared-opening-folders%
Folders may be opened "read-only" by setting the "Open Read Only"
toggle.  You cannot change a folder that is opened read-only, and it
loads somewhat faster, since Z-Mail does not have to make a temporary
working copy.  Z-Mail will automatically mark the folder read-only,
even if the "Open Read Only" toggle is not selected.
