%Forwarding Messages%
%Forwarding_a_Message%

You can forward a message when viewing its
message summary in the Main Window or right
after reading it in the Message Display Window.
In the Main Window,

 - Select it from the Message Summaries list.
 
 - Choose Forward from the Compose menu, or
   click on the Forward button.

The Forward command in the Compose menu opens a
pullright menu.  Choose Resend to send the
message unedited. The Resend dialog opens. Fill
in the address(es) of the intended recipient(s)
and click on the OK button.

Choose Edited to edit or add your comments to
the message. A Compose Window opens that
includes a copy of the original message in the
body of the forward message. The subject of the
original message is added to the subject field
of the forward message, prepended with
"(Fwd)". Edit the message, fill in the
recipient's address, and click on the Send
button.

Choose As Attachments to forward the message as
an attachment of a new message. A Compose
Window opens that includes a copy of the
original message in the Attachments area. The
subject of the original message is added to the
subject field of the forward message, prepended
with "(Fwd)." Write a message, fill in the
recipient's address, and click on the Send
button.

You can forward a message immediately after
reading it, as you go through your new mail. In
the Message Display Window, Click on the
Forward button. A Compose Window opens that
includes a copy of the original message in the
body of the forward message. The subject of the
original message is added to the subject field
of the forward message, prepended with "(Fwd)".
Edit the message, if desired, fill in the
recipient's address, then click on the Send
button.

