%Colors Dialog%
%color_dialog%
The Colors Dialog dialog allows you to interactively change the
colors of some objects on the screen.  You may change entire "classes"
of objects, such as PushButtons or Menus.

Most objects have a "background" and "foreground" color.  Changing the
foreground color of an object affects the object's primary features,
such as the label on a button.  Changing the background affects
everything that's not the foreground, such as the rectangle behind the
label on a button.  

To select a foreground color, click the Foreground toggle and then click
on any color tile.  The foreground of the sample pushbutton will
reflect your choice.  To set the background color, click the Background 
toggle and click on any other color tile.  (You may set both the foreground
and background to the same color, but this will make the objects very
difficult to use.)

Once you've chosen a color scheme, select the types of objects to which
you'd like it applied.  Click Assign to have the new colors appear.

If you like what you've chosen, click the "Save" button.

The file from which Z-Mail retrieves settings from colors saved in this
dialog is identified by the value of the variable ~#colors_db~var#~.  If
~#colors_db~var#~ is not set, the default colors file is .zmcolors in your
home directory.  When you click "Save", an Input popup displays the
current value of ~#colors_db~var#~ and asks you whether to save the colors
there.  You may edit the file name in the Input popup to save colors
to another file.

If you save settings to a file other than that first shown, you must
change the value of ~#colors_db~var#~ in order for Z-Mail to use the colors.
This value can be changed in the Variables dialog.

Unfortunately, due to the nature of the X system, you cannot reset your
colors back to their original settings.  If you wish to revert to the
original colors, you must remove your colors file and restart Z-Mail.
