%Marks and Priorities%
Marks can be used to tag messages for later reference.  They are
temporary and will not be saved when the folder is updated.  To
place a mark on a message, select Mark from the Main Window Edit
menu.

A priority setting using a letter, L (Low), M (Medium), or H (High) 
can also be placed on messages.  Priorities, unlike ordinary marks, are saved when
folders are updated.  Some actions, such as sorting, may be
performed with respect to marks or priorities.  When sorting by
priority, marks have the highest priority, followed by H, B, L, etc.

To set the priority of a message, use the Set Priority pullright from
the Message menu, or from the right-button popup in the Message Summaries
area.  To remove priority, set a priority of "Normal".

Messages may have both a temporary mark and a priority, but may not
have more than one priority.  The presence of a mark is indicated by a
"+", and the presence of a priority is indicated by the priority
letter, immediately following the message's number in the Message
Summaries area.
