%Replying to a Message%
%replying%
To reply to a message, choose one of the four items from the Reply
pullright menu of the Compose menu of the ~#Message Window#~, or press
the 'Reply' or 'ReplyAll' buttons in the Message Window's action area.

When you choose one of these actions, a new composition is started
with the name of the original sender already placed into the To:
field.

The four kinds of Reply are:

  - Reply to sender, which starts a new
    composition and places the name of the address
    to which you're replying into the To: field.

  - Reply to All, which works like Reply to
    Sender, but places all the original recipients
    of the message and the sender in the To:
    field.

  - Reply to Sender (Include), which works like
    Reply to Sender, and also includes a copy of
    the original message, indented, in your comp-
    osition.

  - Reply to All (Include), which works like
    Reply to Sender, and also includes a copy of
    the original message, indented, in your comp-
    osition.

If the variable ~#autoinclude~var#~ is set, "Reply" will automatically
include the message body of the current message in your reply.

If the variable ~#autoedit~var#~ is set, "Reply" will automatically open a
window running the editor specified by your ~#visual~var#~ variable.
