%Search for Pattern%
%Search by Pattern%
%search_dialog%
The Pattern Search dialog lets you search messages in the active
folder, or all the open folders, for a pattern you specify.  Choose
the Pattern Search... item from the Find menu of the ~#Main Window#~
to bring up the Pattern Search dialog.

Use the text fields to specify both the pattern you want to look for
and its location.  You may specify patterns in several of these fields
to help narrow a search. For example, to find all messages from user
"bobg" that contain the phrase "combat boots" in the Subject: field,
you should do the following in the Pattern Search dialog:

  - Enter "bobg" in the From: text field
  - Enter "combat boots" in the Subject: text field

The field marked "Other" is used to search in non-standard
headers.  For example, to find messages that have an
"X-Security-Level" header containing the phrase "top
secret", replace the word "Other:" with "X-Security-Level:"
and type "top secret" in the next text field.

Click Search to begin a search.

When Z-Mail performs a search, it begins by looking for the pattern
specified in the "Other:" field.  If it finds messages that match, it
searches only those messages for the pattern specified in the Subject:
field, if there is one.  It continues searching the From: field, then
the To: field, then the message body, and lastly, the entire message,
if you've specified patterns in any of those fields.

Messages that match the search criteria are selected in the
Main Window, if you have the Select Matches toggle set.  If
you've set the View Only Matches toggle, only matching messages
will be displayed in the Main Window.  (Choose View All from
the View menu in the Main Window to display all the messages
in the current folder.)
