%Sending a Message%
To send your message, click the "Send" button at the bottom
of the ~#Compose Window#~.  The "Messages" menu at the top of
the window provides additional delivery options.  If you
decide you don't want to send the message you're composing,
click the "Cancel" button.  After sending or canceling your
message, click the "Done" button to dismiss the window.

Once you have selected Send, your message is on its way and
cannot be retrieved or canceled.

Click "Cancel" in the popup if you wish to send the message before 
dismissing the Compose Window.  Click "OK" to abort the composition 
and dismiss the Compose Window.

Depending on your Z-Mail configuration, the Compose Window may be
automatically dismissed or iconified when you send or cancel.  The
variables ~#autodismiss~var#~ and ~#autoiconify~var#~ control this behavior.
