%Address Entry%
Enter addresses into the Address Area, which is just below the Messages List 
and just above the Subject Area of a ~#Compose Window#~.
  
To enter an address or addresses:
  
  1. Select an address option by pulling up the Address
     Option Menu, labeled "To:" and in the upper left 
     corner of the Address Area.
  
     Address options and their indications are:
  
       To    Indicates the primary recipients
  
       Cc    Indicates "Carbon copy" recipients
  
       Bcc   Indicates "Blind carbon copy" recipients
  
     Message headers contain lines that indicate 
     recipients in the "To" and "Cc" lists. Recipients 
     in the "Bcc" list are not recorded in out-bound mail.
  
  2. Type the recipient's address in the Address Entry 
     Area, which is to the right of the Address Option 
     Menu. 
  
     You can type in more than one address in the Address 
     Entry Area, provided you separate local addresses with 
     spaces:
  
       pat chris robin shawn
  
     When typing in more than one complex address, separate 
     the addresses with commas and spaces:
  
       pat@circus.com, chris@daisies.org, robin@buzzer.edu
  
     If an address is more complex than those above, you
     will probably want to type in one address only.
  
  3. After typing in the address or addresses, press RETURN. 
     After pressing RETURN, Z-Mail adds the address to the
     Address List, which is below the Address Entry Area
     and above the Subject Area. 
  
To add an address to your address list at any time during your message composition,
repeat the steps listed above.
  
For information on address forms, please refer to ~#Address Forms#~.
