%Buttons Dialog%
%buttons_dialog%

The Buttons dialog is used to create or modify buttons in
the ~#Main Window#~, the ~#Message Display Window#~, or 
the ~#Compose Window#~.

Select the window containing the buttons you wish to modify.  The
scrolled list contains the names of the currently installed buttons
for that window.

To create a new button, click Clear.  To modify an existing button,
select its name in the scrolled list.

The Button: field contains the text that will appear on the button.
The Type: may be Action or Toggle.  Toggle buttons are used to change
the state of some setting between ON and OFF; "edit headers" is a good
example of something that a toggle button may be used for.  Action
buttons perform a one-time action once they are clicked such as "Send"
or "Cancel".

To create toggle buttons, Choose Toggle Button Value... from the 
Options menu to specify the setting that button controls.

The Z-Script field contains the name of the Z-Script command or
function to be executed when the button is clicked. This field
is required for action buttons, but is optional for toggle buttons.

To see all the available functions, or to create a new function, click
the Edit Functions button.  The Functions dialog appears.  To insert
the name of a function into the Z-Script field in the Submenu dialog,
double-click on its name in the Editable Functions list in the
Functions dialog.

See ~#Commands#~ for more information about available commands.

When you have filled in all the text fields for the button, click
Install.

%%

%Menus Dialog%
The Menus dialog is used to customize the following
menus:

 - ~#Main Window#~ menu bar
 - ~#Message summaries#~ pop-up
 - output area pop-up
 - command area pop-up
 - ~#Message display#~ Window menu bar
 - message body pop-up
 - ~#Compose Window#~ menu bar

To edit a menu on a menu bar, click the name of
the window in the Window: area.  To modify a pop-up
menu, select it from the Popups menu.

Modifying Menus on the Menu Bar

Using this dialog, you may:

 - create new menus and their contents
 - add, remove, or modify items on existing menus.

To add, remove, or modify items on existing menus,
begin by selecting the name of the menu in the scrolled
list.  Then click Edit Submenu.  A Submenu dialog
appears, displaying the contents of the menu you
selected.

Use the scrolled list in the Submenu dialog to
specify which item you would like to modify.
To add a new item to the displayed menu, click
Clear.

The Menu: text field contains the name of the
menu item.  The Type: may be one of the
following:

 - Action menus execute a one-time action, 
   such as Read, Send, or Save.

 - Toggle menus change the state of some
   setting, such as Edit Headers or Autoformat.

 - Separators are the lines that sometimes
   appear between items on a menu.  They
   have no function.

 - Submenus are "pullright" menus such as
   the Priority submenu on the Message menu 
   in the Main Window.

If Submenu is selected, the Submenu: field
and Edit Submenu button become active; if you
click Edit Submenu, another Submenu dialog 
appears displaying the contents of the submenu.

The Z-Script field contains the Z-Script command
or function to be executed when the item is
chosen.  

To see all the available functions, or
to create a new function, click the Edit Functions
button.  The Functions dialog appears.  To insert
the name of a function into the Z-Script field
in the Submen dialog, double-click on its name
in the Editable Functions list in the Functions
dialog.

If messages or text must be selected in order for
the specified Z-Script function to work, click
the Requires selected messages box.

The Mnemonic: field contains the character that
may be used in combination with the Meta key
to execute that item without using the mouse.
The Accelerator field contains the keyboard
shortcut that may be used to execute the same
command.  This text also appears on the menu.

To delete a menu or item, select it in the scrolled
list and click Delete.

To change the location of  an item, select it and choose 
Cut Menu Item(s) from the Edit menu in the dialog box.  
Select the item directly beneath the place where you
want the cut item to appear and choose Paste Menu
Item(s).

When you have filled in the fields in this dialog,
click Install.

Modifying Popup Menus

To modify a popup menu, select it from the Popups
menu in the Menus dialog.  The dialog that appears
is equivalent to the Submenu dialog described
above.
